deferred-debugger-remote-cad — Phase 9: remote native-AutoLISP backend (alfe)
=============================================================================

See also:
  clautolisp/documentation/clautolisp-debugger-implementation-plan.org (Phase 9, §1.3)
  clautolisp/documentation/clautolisp-debugger-remote-cad-spec.org (the addendum)
  autolisp-front-end/source/file-protocol.lisp (current alfe<->CAD transport)

DEFERRED — runs after the in-image debugger (Phases 0–7) and is gated on a
transport that satisfies REQ-T1.

Context
-------

The addendum re-targets the APPLICATION side of the Part-III contract to
native AutoLISP inside BricsCAD/AutoCAD, driven over a wire from alfe. The
debugger library, inspector, and three UIs are reused UNCHANGED (the §12/§17
signatures do not change). The single overturned tenet is "same image, no
wire" — debugger<->application becomes a wire protocol, and the parent's
"synchronous, message-free inspection" (§8.3) becomes RPC (addendum §0.1).

TRANSPORT BLOCKER: alfe<->CAD today is file-IPC (atomic writes + status
polling, file-protocol.lisp) — batch/poll oriented, NOT readable
mid-evaluation, so it FAILS REQ-T1. Live breakpoints/stepping need a new
synchronous control channel (socket/pipe); otherwise only POST-MORTEM mode
(break-on-error + reconstructed backtrace) is conformant and MUST be
advertised via `*protocol-version*` capability flags (addendum R-VIII §11).
Open question R-XII.3 to reconcile with the user/author.

Scope (addendum R-XI phasing)
-----------------------------

1. Transport + framing (REQ-T1..T3, P1..P3): prove a pause nests inside an
   in-flight :eval and one :eval-in-frame round-trips; reuse the §20.1
   S-expr RPC shape. Decide socket vs post-mortem for v1.
2. `aldbg:` AutoLISP runtime on the backend: *debug-flag*, breakpoint table,
   Bloom bits, aldbg:pp, aldbg:enter/exit, pause loop (R-III.1–R-III.3).
3. `clautolisp.debug.remote` + instrumenter retargeted to emit ~ord/~dbg
   AutoLISP bodies with source-level Fjeld propagation;
   autolisp-compile[-file]; all §7 metadata stays in alfe (R-II).
4. Breakpoints / stepping / backtrace / innermost eval end-to-end (R-IX "Full").
5. Inspector over the wire: proxies + backend accessor evaluation (R-IV).
6. Error integration: *error*, vl-catch-all, ERRNO, continue-with-return for
   instrumented forms (R-III.7).
7. "Partial" rows + hardening: shadowed-binding read/write, outer-frame eval,
   conditions (set-time $N snapshot), tracing, cooperative interrupt,
   reactor reentrancy, command-input, namespaces, BricsCAD/AutoCAD shim.

Acceptance (when unblocked)
---------------------------

- A parent-conformant UI drives a live (or post-mortem, per transport) debug
  session against AutoLISP running in a real CAD engine; the R-IX fidelity
  matrix rows marked Full are achieved for the chosen transport tier.
